<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.241893>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Phrynus perrii sp. nov. Female paratype: A. Dorsal view of carapace. B. Ventral view of sternum. C. Prolateral and retrolateral surface of chelicera. D. Frontal process of carapace. E. Dorsal view of gonopods." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/241893/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.241894>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Phrynus perrii sp. nov. Female paratype: A. Right trochanter, dorsal view. B. Right femur, dorsal view. C. Left trochanter, ventral view. D. Left femur, ventral view. E. Right patella, dorsal view. F. Right tibia, dorsal view. G. Left patella, ventral view. H. Left tibia, ventral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/241894/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.241895>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Known distribution of Phrynus perrii sp. nov. Orange pentagon: Cueva del Naranjo, Chiapas (type locality); along with the type localities of two other species of Phrynus found in Chiapas." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/241895/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

